Brief project name/idea will be great

Brief project name/idea will be great
We practiced customer interviews in class. I was not expecting you to pick this question as your first question. It does not touch the customer’s direct pain. Competitive analysis table could be more insightful. No screenshots

No Report outline (Overview). Difficult to identify separate sections of your report. Competitive analysis table could be more insightful +/- doesn’t give much information. Seems you have other questions which you didn’t add at the moment.

No Report outline (Overview/Agenda).
No screenshots of mentioned applications. Competitive analysis table could be more descriptive
It is ok that your requirements change. I am happy your team reorganised to make sure the project succeeds

Grammar typos. Not detailed enough feature analysis. Inconvenient to compare the table because of screenshots inside the table. Screenshots also have to explain features, not just to demonstrate general view of a service
No project title. Too many links, it is not convenient to jump between different documents. At least interview script could be inserted.

The number of answers does not correspond to number of questions, no transcript. More detailed answers are required, and summarizing could be done later in the end of the report. If you were missing space, you could use extra link. Duplicated Reflection points, questions to customer, etc.

No project title. The sound in the video record is not loud enough. It is preferred not to type too close to microphone, because it creates additional noise. Do you have any questions left after the interview? Presence of references is very positive

The number of answers does not correspond to number of interview questions, no transcript. More detailed answers are required, and summarizing could be done later in the end of the report. The conversation doesn’t look structured, spaces between monologues of customer doesn’t look like a good interview. Especially, Russian chatting on the background doesn’t look good. Customer looks like the main person just delivering his ideas, while he should be asked to answer your questions. TODO list is very vague

No project title. Interview script is not equal to content of interview. For this separately interview had to be provided. Unclear why music plays on the background of a record, it disturbs the interview and creates problems with listening.

No project title. Interview script is not equal to content of interview. For this separately interview had to be provided. Screenshots are unreadable, no link to source. Publications are not competing tools, only 1 publication has a code source. Are there any existing tools? Typos in the text present. Excel is not a database. The report is very superficial, hard to get the main ideas, it is written for not the external but internal person, this doesn’t seem right.

No project title and document title. The structure could have been done better. Screenshots are not fully readable. Feature design seems to be hard to compare, unclear how it was done. Probably feature name had to be stated differently. The client is not interested in students attending sport classes but to make them do sports in general. Therefore, it is important in transcript to provide the text of a conversation, not to generalize in part related to interview transcript. Here is how you can avoid some problems
For interview transcript it’s better to use the exact words instead of rephrasing. This may reduce the problems with interpretation. The screenshots could have been added from used competitors

No project title. Instead of the link to an audio the pdf’s first page is illustrated. Interview script is not equal to content of interview. Unclear what products are compared in the table. No links to source files of screenshots
